  "prompt": "My girlfriend for 4years cheated 3 times. I found out 2 month ago. She started talking to a guy as a friend. He called her babe, what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through this difficult situation. It's important to prioritize your well-being and consider what you need in a relationship. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to think about how you feel about the relationship and her actions. Consider whether you can or want to rebuild trust.\n\n2. **Communicate**: Have an open and honest conversation with your girlfriend about what happened and how it has affected you. Share your feelings and concerns, and listen to her perspective as well.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the relationship, discuss and establish clear boundaries to prevent similar issues in the future.\n\n4. **Consider Counseling**: Both individual and couple's counseling can be helpful in navigating the emotions and challenges you're facing. A professional can provide support and guidance.\n\n5. **Evaluate Trust**: Trust is foundational in any relationship. Think about whether you can rebuild trust and if both of you are committed to doing so.\n\n6. **Make a Decision**: Ultimately, you need to decide whether staying in the relationship is right for you. Consider what will make you happy and healthy in the long run.\n\nRemember, it's okay to prioritize your own emotional well-being, and seeking support from friends, family, or a professional can be beneficial during this time.",
